OL,3,CSupreme Court to rule on motor finance
OL,4,Ccompensation row
OL,6,FThe court found that three motorists,
OL,7,Fwho all bought their cars before 2021,
OL,8,Fhad not been told either clearly
OL,9,Fenough or at all that the car dealers,
OL,10,Facting as credit brokers, would
OL,11,Freceive a commission from the lenders
OL,12,Ffor introducing business to them, and
OL,13,Fshould receive compensation.
OL,15,FTwo lenders, FirstRand Bank and Close
OL,16,FBrothers, took the row to the Supreme
OL,17,FCourt, telling a three-day hearing in
OL,18,FApril that the decision was an
OL,19,F"egregious error".
