OL,3,CSupreme Court to rule on motor finance
OL,4,Ccompensation row
OL,6,FAfter the claims reached the Court of
OL,7,FAppeal, three senior judges ruled that
OL,8,Fthe lenders were liable to repay the
OL,9,Fmotorists the commission, as there was
OL,10,F"no disclosure" of the commission
OL,11,Fpayments in Ms Hopcraft's case, and
OL,12,F"insufficient disclosure" in the case
OL,13,Fof Mr Wrench.
OL,15,FIn Mr Johnson's case, the judges found
OL,16,Fthat he had received "insufficient
OL,17,Fdisclosure" about the commission to
OL,18,Fgive "fully informed consent" to the
OL,19,Fpayment.
