OL,3,CSupreme Court to rule on motor finance
OL,4,Ccompensation row
OL,6,FLady Justice Andrews, Lord Justice
OL,7,FBirss and Lord Justice Edis said that
OL,8,Fwhile each case was different,
OL,9,F"burying such a statement in the small
OL,10,Fprint which the lender knows the
OL,11,Fborrower is highly unlikely to read
OL,12,Fwill not suffice" as enough to
OL,13,Fproperly inform a motorist about the
OL,14,Fcommission.
OL,16,FIf justices dismiss the challenge, it
OL,17,Fis unclear how many people could be
OL,18,Fentitled to compensation.
